{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "afac14a1-d436-43fc-8691-393b13e27c9a",
    "name": "RentNest API",
    "description": "# RentNest — Rental Property Marketplace API\n\nA backend API for a rental marketplace where landlords list properties, tenants browse and request to rent them, payments are handled via Stripe, and admins moderate the platform.\n\n## Auth model\nThis API uses **httpOnly cookies** (`accessToken`, `refreshToken`), not a Bearer token header. Run **Login User** once in this collection and Postman's cookie jar will automatically attach the cookie to every subsequent request against the same `baseUrl` — no manual header setup needed.\n\n## Roles\n- **TENANT** — browses properties, submits rental requests, pays rent, leaves reviews\n- **LANDLORD** — manages their own property listings, approves/rejects requests on those properties\n- **ADMIN** — manages users and has full platform oversight\n\n## Response format\nEvery endpoint returns a consistent JSON envelope:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"StatusCodes\": 200,\n  \"message\": \"Human-readable description of what happened\",\n  \"data\": { /* the actual payload, or null */ },\n  \"Meta\": { \"page\": 1, \"limit\": 10, \"total\": 42 } // only present on paginated list endpoints\n}\n```\nError responses use the same envelope shape, with `success: false` and an added `error` field.\n\n## Before you start\n1. Set the `baseUrl` collection variable (see Variables tab) to your local server (`http://localhost:5000`) or your deployed URL.\n2. Run **01 - Authentication → Register User**, then **Login User**.\n3. You're now authenticated for the rest of the collection.\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "54716308"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 - Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register User",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Himu Rahman\",\n  \"email\": \"himu@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass123\",\n  \"role\": \"TENANT\",\n  \"phone\": \"0168364407\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/register",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "users",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Create a new account as a **TENANT** or **LANDLORD**. Public endpoint — no login required.\n\nAdmin accounts cannot be self-registered; they must be created directly in the database or promoted by an existing admin."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login User",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"himu@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass123\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate with email + password. On success, sets `accessToken` and `refreshToken` as httpOnly cookies. Public endpoint — do NOT attach any existing token to this request."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Access Token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh-token",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "refresh-token"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Issues a new `accessToken` using the `refreshToken` cookie set at login. Call this when an authenticated request starts returning 401 due to an expired access token."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Public endpoints for registering, logging in, and refreshing a session. Login and refresh set `accessToken` / `refreshToken` as **httpOnly cookies** — Postman's cookie jar carries them automatically on later requests in this collection, so you do not need to add an Authorization header manually."
    },
